messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyUI_rotate_image custom node?
The ComfyUI_rotate_image custom node is designed to rotate images in ComfyUI.
Yes, ComfyUI_rotate_image is an Img2Img node in ComfyUI.
Can ComfyUI_rotate_image be used to rotate images generated by other nodes in ComfyUI?
Yes, as an Img2Img node, ComfyUI_rotate_image can be used to rotate images generated by other nodes in ComfyUI.
Does ComfyUI_rotate_image have any additional functionality besides rotating images?
The provided information does not specify any additional functionality of ComfyUI_rotate_image besides rotating images.
Is ComfyUI_rotate_image a built-in node or a custom node in ComfyUI?
ComfyUI_rotate_image is a custom node in ComfyUI.
Can ComfyUI_rotate_image be used for image generation or only for image manipulation?
ComfyUI_rotate_image is an Img2Img node, which means it is primarily used for image manipulation, specifically for rotating images.
Is there any limitation on the image format that can be processed by ComfyUI_rotate_image?
The provided information does not specify any limitations on the image format that can be processed by ComfyUI_rotate_image.
